album.name: Nordic Metal - A Tribute To Euronymous

wiki.summary: Trivia "From Booklet" The Nordic Metal Compilation CD is dedicated to Euronymous. The king of all kings... (15/04/68 - 10/08/93). Executive Producers: 'Typhon' and 'Euronymous'. Compiled by: Öystein 'Euronymous' Aarseth and Paul 'Typhon' Thind. Mastered at: Armageddon Studios, Northern California. So what you are looking at now is not another 'Compilation', but a testimony, if you will, to the man who singlehandedly, revived the 'New Age of Black Metal' in Norway. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Trivia "From Booklet" The Nordic Metal Compilation CD is dedicated to Euronymous. The king of all kings... (15/04/68 - 10/08/93). Executive Producers: 'Typhon' and 'Euronymous'. Compiled by: Öystein 'Euronymous' Aarseth and Paul 'Typhon' Thind. Mastered at: Armageddon Studios, Northern California. So what you are looking at now is not another 'Compilation', but a testimony, if you will, to the man who singlehandedly, revived the 'New Age of Black Metal' in Norway. The bands featured on this release come together for a reason that they don't expect all to understand. Each one of them had their own special relationship with Euronymous and were proud to be a part of this monumental tribute. They are all excellent at what they do. They are the new kings, the creators, the originators of their new breeds of 'Nordic Metal'. My dark Hails to them all... - Paul 'Typhon' Thind Necropolis Records Track 12 misspelled as "Rodt Og Svart" Read more on Last.fm.
